<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font face="arial" style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><br><font face="arial">Thanks for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.</font><br><br><font face="arial">We are writing to confirm that, as per your request,&nbsp;</font><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">we have cancelled your insurance policy&nbsp;<i>(insert policy number or Add on product name)</i></b><font face="arial">&nbsp;with Kingsbridge.&nbsp;</font><br><br>To confirm,&nbsp;<b>your policy was active for the period&nbsp;<i>(DDMMYYYY to DDMMYYYY)</i></b>.&nbsp;<br><br><br><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Cancelling your payment</b><br><br><font face="arial">As you paid in a single payment, a pro-rata refund of&nbsp;</font><i style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">£XXX</i><font face="arial">&nbsp;will appear in the account from which you originally paid in the next 3 to 10 working days.</font><br><br><br><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Making a claim</b><br><br><i style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">(Use if for IR35)&nbsp;</i><font face="arial">IR35 Protect operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, so the policy must be active to respond to most claims. However, for&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">sections 10-12</a><font face="arial">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</font><font face="arial">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.</font><br><br><i style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">(Use for Legal Expenses)</i><font face="arial">&nbsp;Legal Expenses cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. However, for&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">section 10</a><font face="arial">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</font><font face="arial">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.</font><br><br><i style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">(Use for Cyber Liability)&nbsp;</i><font face="arial">Cyber Liability cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. For some sections of the cover however, you can notify us of a claim up to 30 days following your policy expiry date</font><font face="arial">. Please see your&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">policy wording</a><font face="arial">&nbsp;for full details.</font><br><br><font face="arial">If you are unsure whether you can make a claim on a cancelled policy, please contact our customer service team and we will be happy to help.</font></div><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><br>Whether you’re currently insured with Kingsbridge or not, our customer service team is always here to help. Please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.<br><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br><span style="font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>